      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: YouTube subscriptions management and playlist write commands",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds write-capable YouTube commands covering two areas:\n\n**Subscriptions (`gog youtube subscriptions`)**\n- `list` — list subscriptions for the authenticated account, with `--all` for automatic pagination across all pages\n- `subscribe --channel-id ID` — subscribe to a channel (with `--dry-run` support)\n- `unsubscribe --id ID` / `--channel-id ID` — unsubscribe by subscription ID or channel ID, with confirmation prompt and `--dry-run` support\n\n**Playlists (`gog youtube playlists create / add`)**\n- `create --title TITLE [--description DESC] [--privacy public|unlisted|private]` — create a new playlist for the authenticated account\n- `add --playlist-id ID --video-id ID [--position N]` — add a video to a playlist (appends by default, or at a specific 0-based position)\n\nAll commands follow existing patterns: `--account`, `-j`/`--json`, `--plain`, `--dry-run` where appropriate.\n\n**OAuth scope change**\n\nThe `ServiceYouTube` registration is updated from `youtube.readonly` to the full `youtube` scope. This is required for all write operations (subscribe, unsubscribe, playlist create/add). Read-only operations are unaffected; callers using an API key bypass OAuth entirely.\n\n> **Note for reviewers:** If you'd prefer write operations use a separate service registration to keep the default read-only, I'm happy to refactor — e.g. a `ServiceYouTubeWrite` alongside the existing readonly one, following the `NewYouTubeCommentsForAccount` pattern. Let me know your preference.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `gog youtube subscriptions list --account ACCOUNT` returns subscriptions\n- [x] `gog youtube subscriptions list --all --account ACCOUNT` paginates through all pages\n- [x] `gog youtube subscriptions subscribe --channel-id UC... --account ACCOUNT` subscribes\n- [x] `gog youtube subscriptions unsubscribe --channel-id UC... --dry-run --account ACCOUNT` prints what would be removed without acting\n- [x] `gog youtube playlists create --title \"Test\" --privacy unlisted --account ACCOUNT` creates and returns playlist ID\n- [x] `gog youtube playlists add --playlist-id PL... --video-id ... --account ACCOUNT` adds video\n- [x] Existing `gog youtube playlists list` and all read commands continue to work\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
